  "text": "Smoking status was classified by the number of cigarettes smoked per day, according to a report by Pfeilschifter and Ziegler [CITATION_1] as follows: 0, no smoking; 1, <10 cigarettes/day; 2, 10-20 cigarettes/day; and 3, >20 cigarettes/day. All smokers were current smokers at the first examination, while all nonsmokers had not experienced smoking in their life.",
